#

Spicy Korean Fried Chicken with Kimchi Slaw

$20
600 kcal
Difficulty: 70%
Servings: 4

Allergens:

SoyGluten

Dietary Tags:

SpicyKoreanFriedPoultry

Tags:

SpicyFriedKoreanPoultryDinner

Description

Crispy, spicy Korean-style fried chicken served with a tangy, crunchy kimchi slaw that balances heat with freshness.

Ingredients

  • Chicken wings: 1.5 lbs
  • Cornstarch: 1 cup
  • All-purpose flour: 1/2 cup
  • Salt: 1 tsp
  • Black pepper: 1/2 tsp
  • Garlic powder: 1 tsp
  • Gochujang (Korean chili paste): 1/4 cup
  • Soy sauce: 2 tbsp
  • Honey: 2 tbsp
  • Rice vinegar: 1 tbsp
  • Sesame oil: 1 tsp
  • Vegetable oil: for frying
  • Kimchi: 1 cup, chopped
  • Green cabbage: 2 cups, shredded
  • Carrot: 1, julienned
  • Green onions: 2, chopped
  • Mayonnaise: 1/4 cup
  • Lime juice: 1 tbsp
